g.aria-label: Projected Crop Demand Growth from 2005-2050Projected food demand increases from 2005 to 2050. Overall demand is predicted byTilman et al.;meat, sugarcane/beet, oilcrop, and cereal are predicted byAlexandratos and Bruinsma, and maize,rice, wheat, and soybean are predicted byRay et al.Tilman, D., Balzer C., Hill, J, and Befort, B. "Global food demand and the sustainable intensification of agriculture".Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America108(5) pp. 20260–20264.October 2011.Alexandratos, N., Bruinsma, J. "World Agriculture Toward 2030/2050: The 2012 Revision". Global Perspective StudiesTeam, Agricultural Development Economics Division, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.June 2012.Ray, D., Mueller, N., West, P., Foley, J. "Yield Trends Are Insufficient to Double Global Crop Production by 2050". PLoSONE8(6): e66428.June 2013.
